{"response":"success","html":"<div id='dialog-intro' title='Installation complete!'>\n\t<div class='intro-t'>\n\t\t<h1>Welcome to the `<i>Yet Another Monitor<\/i>` reports!<\/h1>\n\t\t<p>The good news is that you've gotten to this page so it looks like everything has been installed properly!<\/p>\n\t\t<p>Just a few more clicks and you can see the reports.<\/p>\n\t<\/div>\n\t<div class='intro-t hidden'>\n\t\t<h1>What's happening?<\/h1>\n\t\t<p>You are now using a fork of Al Caugheys YAMon4 package. This is the full local installation and is as complete it can be considering the absence of Al Caugheys (the original author and developer) involvement.</p><p>During the YAMon4 setup, you were given an option to use Als original site (and its files) in your installation, or to make the installation a fully local one. This (page) identifies it as being a local installation and therefore the .png(etc), .css and *.js files (found in the images/, css/, and js/ directories) are sourced directly from this local installation.</p><p> You can now edit those files and any edits / changes will remain after a reload. They will not be overwritten (backups are still your friend).</p>\t\t<p>This also means that if (or when) usage-monitoring.com ceases to exist, YAMon4 will continue to work from this local configuration.</p><br><p>The parent site at usage-monitoring.com does not appear to be maintained any more. The database integration has gone and if you had a dbkey, it will not work.</p><br><p>In truth, being unmaintained and long in the tooth. I don't have a high trust level on usage-monitoring.com anymore.</p><br><p>If what follows is a broken image, then the site has gone.</p><p> <img src='\/\/usage-monitoring.com\/images\/report-tabs.png'><\/p>\n\t\t<p>Instead, if it shows you the tabs image, then go and visit the rest of the help pages while they remain.\n\t Visit the <a href='https:\/\/usage-monitoring.com\/reports.php' target='_blank'>Reports</a> page at https:\/\/usage-monitoring.com\/ for a more detailed description of each report.<\/p>\n\t<\/div>\n\t<div class='intro-t hidden'>\n\t\t<h1><span class='settings-tab settings'><\/span>Javascript<\/h1>\n\t\t<p>If you know your way around javascript code then you may be able to rejig this code to prevent this page from showing. (I don't and I can't). So, you're stuck with yet another click before you get to the meat in the sandwich.<\/p></br><p>But, while we're here. Remember you can still access the original www.usage-monitoring.com and its files (that may still exist) by enabling the doLocalFile key   in the <em>/opt/YAMon4/config.file</em>.</p></br><b><p>_doLocalFiles='1'  # make a local copy of JS, CSS and images: 0-&gt;no (this will use the offsite files) || 1-&gt;yes (this will use your local files)</b></p><br><p>Having a full local installation will allow development and bug fixes to the code to be preserved.</p><p>Any issues, bug fixes, improvements to this code version can be made at it's <a href='https:\/\/github.com\/glennmckechnie\/YAMon-v4' target='_blank'>github repo</a>; create an issue there or otherwise communicate it to me.</p>\n\t<\/div>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/div>"}
